6 Subject: Firearms; voluntary storage program
7 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to establish a
8 voluntary program in which persons in crisis would have the opportunity to
9 temporarily relinquish their firearms to federally licensed firearms dealers.
10 The program would include the following elements:
11 (1) Federally licensed firearms dealers in Vermont would have the
12 option to choose to participate in a temporary firearms storage program for
13 persons in crisis.
14 (2) A person experiencing a mental health or other relevant crisis could
15 bring their firearms to a participating firearms dealer for temporary
16 safekeeping.
17 (3) The program would authorize participating dealers to temporarily
18 store the person’s firearms until the person is no longer in crisis. The program
19 would provide criminal and civil immunity from liability to participating
20 dealers for any harm resulting from the dealer’s acceptance, storage, return, or
